#U theme vowels behave haphazardly
#For optional variants, can't determine which is preferred form
:Indc VerbRootUc(1) VZero VerbRootUc(2): ThU Pres0 PresAgr Indc: 
:Indc VerbRootUc(1) VZero VerbRootUc(2): ThU|ThE ImpfAgr Indc:
:Indc VerbRootNulV(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulV(2): ThU Pres0 PresAgr Indc: 
:Indc VerbRootNulV(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulV(2): ThE ImpfAgr Indc: 
:Indc VerbRootNulC(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulC(2): ThU Pres0 PresAgr Indc: 
:Indc VerbRootNulC(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulC(2): ThE ImpfAgr Indc: 


PATTERN SubjunctiveIrregular
#These have an irregular indicative form that lacks prefix
VerbRootCanShort(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootCanShort(2): ThA Pres0 PresAgr Indc:  #  
VerbRootCanShort(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootCanShort(2): ThA ImpfAgr Indc: #  

 #U theme vowels with C-initial segment behave haphazardly
#For optional variants, can't determine which is preferred form in some cases
#I let it overgeneralize the -e- form to negation even though the grammar only shows -u-
VerbRootUc(1) VZero VerbRootUc(2): ThU|ThE Pres0 PresAgr Subj0
VerbRootUc(1) VZero VerbRootUc(2): ThU|ThE ImpfAgr Subj0
VerbRootNulV(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulV(2): ThU Pres0 PresAgr Subj0
VerbRootNulV(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulV(2): ThU|ThE ImpfAgr Subj0 #Overgeneralize because no negative form, and not clear about -e- in complex tenses
VerbRootNulC(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulC(2):  ThU  Pres0 PresAgr Subj0
VerbRootNulC(1) EmptyNasal VZero VerbRootNulC(2):  ThE ImpfAgr Subj0



